      "bugs": [],
      "raw_response": "{\n  \"verdict\": \"FAIL\",\n  \"bugs\": [\n    {\n      \"description\": \"The algorithm never updates the result array; it never marks any player as a potential winner, so output is always all zeros (except n==1).\",\n      \"line\": 12,\n      \"severity\": \"critical\",\n      \"triggering_input\": \"1\\n2\\n1 2\\n1 2\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"description\": \"The inner loop logic is incorrect: it attempts to expand max_a and max_b but the condition `if a[i] < max_a or b[i] < max_b:` is wrong and does not reflect the tournament rules. It also incorrectly updates `changed` and may miss players that should be reachable.\",\n      \"line\": 20,\n      \"severity\": \"major\",\n      \"triggering_input\": \"1\\n3\\n1 3 2\\n1 2 3\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"description\": \"The variable `count` is incremented for every examined player but never used; the comment indicates wrong counting, showing incomplete implementation.\",\n      \"line\": 26,\n      \"severity\": \"minor\",\n      \"triggering_input\": \"1\\n2\\n5 1\\n5 1\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"description\": \"The algorithm attempts to run a BFS for each start player but never stores or aggregates the reachable players, making the whole approach O(n^2) and incorrect for large n (up to 1e5). This leads to TLE risk and wrong results.\",\n      \"line\": 14,\n      \"severity\": \"critical\",\n      \"triggering_input\": \"1\\n100000\\n\" + \" \".join(str(i) for i in range(1,100001)) + \"\\n\" + \" \".join(str(i) for i in range(100001,200001))\n    },\n    {\n      \"description\": \"The code uses the variable `n` from the outer scope but also redefines it inside `solve()`. While this works, the outer `t` loop calls `solve()` which reads its own `n`; however, the outer `t` variable is not used inside `solve`, which is fine but could be confusing.\",\n      \"line\": 6,\n      \"severity\": \"minor\",\n      \"triggering_input\": \"1\\n1\\n100\\n100\"\n    }\n  ]\n}",
